Subject: Re: [T2]  Weber 48 IDA Value & Marvel Mystery Oil

48 IDA's are way to big for any street car.  You can try it all you want,
but you will spend a fortune jetting and re-jetting....................

All the motors you mentioned from the VW rags are
hot-rods..................They are not daily drivers.  The people that own
these take them off a trailer at the shows and probably drag them.

Much better off to get carbs that are close to the size you need to start
with.  Those 48's look impressive, but few cars can use them, and even fewer
people have the patience, money and experience to tune them right.


Adam P

