> I'll refer to page 50 of the November 2000 edition of Hot VW's featuring a
blue 65 Type1 with a 1915cc engine & twin 48 IDA's.
> Or perhaps the 54 Oval featured on page 48 in this year's February edition
of Hot VW's running a 1835cc with twin 48 IDA's.
> And perhaps you'd like to tell Frenchy Dehoux of all people that when he
built this car he was building a engine that wouldn't even run & would
"flood the plugs before you could get them to fire on initial startup".
> You might also want to tell him that the 36mm venturis he's running are
way wrong as well.
> Or perhaps take a look in the same edition at Geoff Hart's 10 second
2332cc equipped 59 Sunroof bug that runs bored our 52mm IDA's with 46mm
venturis.
> This last one is maybe a bit much because it's practically a drag car, has
no back seat, spindle front wheels & a full rollcage.
> My point is that IDA's are alive & well on VW's & providing amazing
results.
> Oh, & your point on Marvel Mystery Oil.
> In a tech article on rebuilding Weber & Dellorto carbs sponsored by CB
Perfromance in again the same edition readers are advised to use either
Liquid Wrench or.......surprise, surprise....Marvel Mystery Oil & the
technical staff actually used the Marvel product.
> I'm sure your methods are excellent Tim & your years of experience has
